<L><MILESTONE N="250">But thou <HI>Eumaeus,</HI> as 'tis born away,</L>
<L>Thy ma&s;ter's weapon to his hand convey.</L>
<L>At ev'ry portal let &s;ome matron wait,</L>
<L>And each lock fa&s;t the well-compacted gate:</L>
<L>Clo&s;e let them keep, whate'er invades their ear;</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="255">Tho' arms, or &s;houts, or dying groans they hear.</L>
<L>To thy &s;trict charge, <HI>Philaetius!</HI> we con&s;ign</L>
<L>The court's main gate: To guard that pa&s;s be thine.</L>
<L>This &s;aid, he fir&s;t return'd: the faithful &s;wains</L>
<L>At di&s;tance follow, as their King ordains.</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="260">Before the flame <HI>Eurymachus</HI> now &s;tands,</L>
<L>And turns the bow, and chafes it with his hands:</L>
<L>Still the tough bow unmov'd. The lofty man</L>
<L>Sigh'd from his mighty &s;oul, and thus began</L>
