<L>Oh cur&s;t event! and oh unlook'd-for aid!<MILESTONE N="265"></L>
<L><HI>Melanthius</HI> or the women have betray'd&mdash;</L>
<L><PB N="118" REF="116">
Oh my dear &s;on!&mdash;The father with a &s;igh:</L>
<L>Then ceas'd; the filial virtue made reply.</L>
<L>Fal&s;hood is folly, and 'tis ju&s;t to own</L>
<L>The fault committed; this was mine alone;</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="170">My ha&s;te neglected yonder door to bar,</L>
<L>And hence the villain has &s;upply'd their war.</L>
<L>Run good <HI>Eumaeus</HI> then, and (what before</L>
<L>I thoughtle&s;s err'd in) well &s;ecure that door:</L>
<L>Learn if by female fraud this deed were done,</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="175">Or (as my thought mi&s;gives) by <HI>Dolius</HI>' &s;on.</L>
<L>While yet they &s;poke, in que&s;t of arms again</L>
<L>To the high chamber &s;tole the faithle&s;s &s;wain,</L>
<L>Not unob&s;erv'd. <HI>Eumaeus</HI> watchful ey'd,</L>
<L>And thus addre&s;s'd <HI>Uly&s;&s;es</HI> near his &s;ide.</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="180">The mi&s;creant we &s;u&s;pected takes that way;</L>
<L>Him, if this arm be pow'rful, &s;hall I &s;lay?</L>
<L>Or drive him hither, to receive the meed</L>
<L>From thy own hand, of this dete&s;ted deed?</L>
<L>Not &s;o (reply'd <HI>Uly&s;&s;es</HI>) leave him there,</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="165">For us &s;ufficient is another care:</L>
<L><PB N="119" REF="117">
Within the &s;tricture of this palace wall</L>
<L>To keep inclos'd his ma&s;ters till they fall.</L>
<L>Go you, and &s;eize the felon; backward bind</L>
<L>His arms and legs, and fix a plank behind;</L>
<L>On this, his body by &s;trong cords extend,<MILESTONE N="190"></L>
