<L>Cover'd with du&s;t, with dryne&s;s chapt and worn,</L>
<L>The bra&s;s corroded, and the leather torn:<MILESTONE N="200"></L>
<L>Thus laden, o'er the thre&s;hold as he &s;tept,</L>
<L>Fierce on the villain from each &s;ide they leapt,</L>
<L>Back by the hair the trembling da&s;tard drew,</L>
<L>And down reluctant on the pavement threw.</L>
<L><PB N="120" REF="118">
<MILESTONE N="210">Active and pleas'd, the zealous &s;wains fulfil</L>
<L>At ev'ry point their ma&s;ter's rigid will:</L>
<L>Fir&s;t, fa&s;t behind, his hands and feet they bound,</L>
<L>Then &s;treighten'd cords involv'd his body round;</L>
<L>So drawn aloft, athwart the column ty'd,</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="215">The howling felon &s;wung from &s;ide to &s;ide.</L>
<L><HI>Eumaeus</HI> &s;coffing, then with keen di&s;dain.</L>
<L>There pa&s;s thy plea&s;ing night, oh gentle &s;wain!</L>
