<DIV1 TYPE="argument">
<PB REF="219">
<HEAD>The ARGUMENT.</HEAD>
<P><HI>The &s;ouls of the Suitors are conducted by</HI> Mercury <HI>to the infernal
&s;hades.</HI> Uly&s;&s;es <HI>in the country goes to the retirement of his fa|ther</HI>
Laertes; <HI>he finds him bu&s;yed in his garden all alone: The
manner of his di&s;covery to him is beautifully de&s;cribed. They re|turn
together to his lodge, and the King is acknowledg'd by</HI> Doli|us
<HI>and the &s;ervants. The</HI> Ithacen&s;ians, <HI>led by</HI> Eupithes <HI>the fa|ther
of</HI> Antinous, <HI>ri&s;e again&s;t</HI> Uly&s;&s;es, <HI>who gives them battle, in
which</HI> Eupithes <HI>is killed by</HI> Laertes: <HI>And the Godde&s;s</HI> Pallas
<HI>makes a la&s;ting peace between</HI> Uly&s;&s;es <HI>and his &s;ubjects, which con|cludes
the</HI> Ody&s;&s;ey.</P>
</DIV1>
